<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#00ff00" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Xonan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I recently downloaded EQw and I have a few questions about running multiple copies of everquest at once. First off, here's my system information : <P>Pentium 4 1.5ghz<BR>1 gig of Sdram<BR>Upgraded WindowsXp (from WinMe)<BR>GeForce2 MX400 (the 64mb of ram Geforce 2)<BR>DSL connection to the internet<P>Now, I have been running two copies of eqw. My problem is that when I try to play with both copies up, EQ becomes very choppy display wise. I tried messing with the EQW ini file, changing vsync to false and trying to shut off    the refreshing of EQw when it is in the backround, but this doesn't seem to help as when I switch from copy to copy the other inactive EQw still seems to refresh itself. I'm wondering where the problem lies, whether I need more ram, a faster processor, or a new video card. Being the nature of the problem and how the display becomes choppy, it would lead me to believe the fault lies with my video card. Yet when I ctrl-alt-del while running two copies of EQw, my CPU usage is at 100% which gives me the impression that the CPU is what is holding me back. I'm not sure what I should do, perhaps look into overclocking? Your help would be much appreciated with this  <IMG SRC="http://www.ethernalquest.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">iNCUEBUS</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">not raggin on pentium users but the p4 is horrible =/ my duron 1.0 box outclocks and outperforms a p4 1.2 on any benchmark and runs smoother with games. although the gforce2 had problems with EQ . eitheir way try to lower SOL textures maybe?<P>------------------<BR>************<BR>-iNCUEBUS<BR>************</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">figment</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">What is your CPU usage when running just 1 copy of eqw and eq?<P>Are you running EQ with all the new models on?  if so try turning off all new models and see what happens.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Myztic</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">In device manager disable your sound card, then open EQw</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">RSB</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Problem is that Everquest is a very multi application unfriendly program.  It WILL suck up as much CPU as it can.  things you can do are limit the frame rate via EQW a bit.  Other things ... make sure your AGP Appiture size is set to 256 or 128 as textures will get loaded twice...once for each copy of EQ.<BR>Another thing I do is I run my 2nd EQW on a seperate EQ directory with different settings.  I run with everything off basically and I have no problems.<P>Hope this helps<BR>RSB</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">bvnk3r</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">i tried changing both settings that Myztic and RSB had suggested.  I'm still getting 100% CPU usage with 1 window running and if i load 2 then it's choppy as all hell.  I used to run EQW with 2 accounts about 7 months ago or so.  Had a slower CPU and less memory and never had problems.  Then again i have WinXP and eqw2.2 now.  Which could it be? or maybe it's just EQ? /shrug<BR>would like to be able to run 2 windows again tho  <IMG SRC="http://www.ethernalquest.com/ubb/frown.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Xonan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I want to thank Myztic for his help, because this solved the problem for me at least. It seemed that even with the sounds disabled interally with everquest, the soundcard was still trying to produce them at low volume. I disabled the soundcard and all sound features in windows and EQW runs fine with multiple copies. Thanks again!  <IMG SRC="http://www.ethernalquest.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mr Guy</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If your accounts are unbalanced as far as expansions go, load the one with the least expansion first.<P>For example, I have little trouble if I load my Secondary account with no expansions then load my primary with all three.  If I do it the other way, the primary will completely slurp up my machine, which admittedly is only a 256 RAM machine.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
